fix_multi_drivers(25.10)                              fix_multi_drivers(25.10)

Name
       fix_multi_drivers  -  Fixes multi-drive issues by disconnecting driving
       ports that do not have a real driver

Syntax
       fix_multi_drivers

       [-help]

       [-exclude_net <netName> | <netNameList>]

       [-replace_bus_bit]

       [-report_only]

       Fixes multi-drive issues by disconnecting driving  ports  that  do  not
       have a real driver. The fix_multi_drivers command also works for looped
       multi-driver assign net.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each fix_multi_drivers parameter.

       -exclude_net <netName> | <netNameList>
              Specifies the list of nets to be excluded.

       -replace_bus_bit
              Replaces all bus ports with wrong directions,  if  any,  by  new
              scalar  ports.  If  not  specified, just report without such re-
              placement.

       -report_only
              Reports, but does not fix, ports with wrong directions.

